  </div>

  <main id="main" class="wrap">
    <section id="what" aria-labelledby="what-title">
      <h2 id="what-title">What is credit card fraud?</h2>
      <p>Credit card fraud happens when someone uses a card or card details without authorization to make purchases or withdraw money. It can occur online, by phone, or in person.</p>
      <div class="grid">
        <div>
          <h3>Common categories</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Lost or stolen card used without permission</li>
            <li>Unauthorized online or phone transactions (card‑not‑present)</li>
            <li>Account takeovers through phishing or weak passwords</li>
            <li>Skimming devices capturing card data at compromised terminals</li>
            <li>New accounts opened using stolen personal data (identity theft)</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="note">These examples are provided to improve awareness and prevention—not to enable wrongdoing.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3>Red flags to watch for</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Unexpected transaction alerts or one‑time passcodes you didn’t request</li>
            <li>Emails, texts, or calls asking for passwords, PINs, or full card numbers</li>
            <li>Checkout pages that look off (misspellings, unusual URLs, no HTTPS)</li>
            <li>ATMs or pumps with loose card readers or hidden cameras</li>
            <li>Letters about accounts you didn’t open</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="protect" aria-labelledby="protect-title">
      <h2 id="protect-title">How to protect yourself</h2>
      <div class="cards">
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Secure your accounts</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Use strong, unique passwords and enable multi‑factor authentication</li>
            <li>Set up transaction alerts for all cards</li>
            <li>Consider a credit freeze with major bureaus if you don’t need new credit</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Shop safely</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Use trusted merchants and secure connections (look for HTTPS)</li>
            <li>Avoid saving card details unnecessarily; use virtual card numbers if available</li>
            <li>Be cautious with public Wi‑Fi; avoid purchases on unsecured networks</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Stay alert</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Monitor statements and credit reports regularly</li>
            <li>Beware of unsolicited requests for personal or financial information</li>
            <li>Shred sensitive documents; secure your mailbox</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="respond" aria-labelledby="respond-title" class="steps">
      <h2 id="respond-title">What to do if you suspect fraud</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>Contact your card issuer immediately using the number on the back of your card or their official website. Ask to block the card and review recent charges.</li>
        <li>Change passwords on affected accounts and enable multi‑factor authentication.</li>
        <li>Check recent statements and dispute unauthorized charges promptly. Many issuers offer zero‑liability protection.</li>
        <li>Place a fraud alert or freeze with the credit bureaus to help prevent new accounts from being opened.</li>
        <li>Report the incident to the appropriate authorities (see resources below) and keep copies of all correspondence.</li>
      </ol>
      <p class="note">If your physical card was lost or stolen, also consider filing a local police report. For identity theft, create a personalized recovery plan via official government portals.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="merchants" aria-labelledby="merchants-title">
      <h2 id="merchants-title">For merchants and developers</h2>
      <p class="badge" aria-hidden="true">Best practices</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Comply with PCI DSS requirements for handling cardholder data</li>
        <li>Use tokenization, address verification (AVS), and CVV checks</li>
        <li>Enable 3‑D Secure or similar step‑up authentication for risky transactions</li>
        <li>Implement rate limiting, bot detection, and anomaly monitoring</li>
        <li>Encrypt data in transit and at rest; minimize data retention</li>
        <li>Provide clear customer support channels for disputes and chargebacks</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="note">Developers should never log or store full PANs, full magnetic‑stripe data, or CVV. Follow least‑privilege and secure coding practices.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="report" aria-labelledby="report-title">
      <h2 id="report-title">Report fraud and get help</h2>
      <div class="grid">
        <div>
          <h3>United States</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Report identity theft and create a recovery plan: https://www.identitytheft.gov</li>
            <li>Internet crime complaints (including online fraud): https://www.ic3.gov</li>
            <li>Consumer protection and complaints: https://reportfraud.ftc.gov</li>
            <li>Credit bureaus (freeze or alert):
              <ul>
                <li>Equifax: https://www.equifax.com</li>
                <li>Experian: https://www.experian.com</li>
                <li>TransUnion: https://www.transunion.com</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>Opt out of prescreened offers: https://www.optoutprescreen.com</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3>Other regions</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>EU consumer protection: https://europa.eu/youreurope/citizens/consumers</li>
            <li>UK Action Fraud: https://www.actionfraud.police.uk</li>
            <li>Canada: https://www.antifraudcentre-centreantifraude.ca</li>
            <li>Australia: https://www.scamwatch.gov.au</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="note">If your country isn’t listed, search your government’s official consumer protection or cybercrime reporting site.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="warning" style="margin-top:16px; padding:14px; border-radius:10px;">
        <h3>Important</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Only use official contact numbers and websites for your bank and authorities.</li>
